SQL - Structured Query Language

Table  : Collection of data
Row    : Elements in Table
Column : Field in Row

INSTALL SQLITE3 inn Archlinux
------------------------------
yay -S sqlite3


eg:- file : users.db
-----------------------------------------------------------------
  table:users                                                   | <- table
-----------------------------------------------------------------
id |    name    |   email              |  phone    | password   |
-----------------------------------------------------------------
1  |   john     |    john@gmail.com    | 8009009    | pass123   | <- row
2  |   antony   |    anto98@gmail.com  | 9997776    | abcd111   |
3  |   peter    |    pete4@gmail.com   | 767999     | pil009    |
4  |   milan    |    milan7@gmail.com  | 990088     | yt6@1     | 
-----------------------------------------------------------------
      ^ column

      
QUERIES
--------

1. make/create/open new db file
--------------------------------
sqlite3 users.db 

2. Create schema
-----------------
[in sqlite3]

CREATE TABLE users (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
    name TEXT NOT NULL,
    email TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    phone TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    password TEXT NOT NULL
);

2. INSERT A  NEW ROW
---------------------
INSERT INTO users (name,email,phone,password) VALUES ('lisa','lisa2@gmail.com','998877','lisa666');

3.SELECT
---------
  A. Select all columns (lists all data in the table users)
  -----------------------------------------------------------
  SELECT * FROM users;

  B. Select specific columns (lists only name and email field)
  ------------------------------------------------------------
  SELECT name,phone FROM users;

  C.  Select clause with conditions
  ----------------------------------
  SELECT * FROM users WHERE email='anto98@gmail.com' AND password='abcd111';

  result: 2|antony|anto98@gmail.com|9997776|abcd111


